episodes.title: An Eyewitness Account | Cult Massacre: One Day in Jonestown | National Geographic UK
episodes.description:
In the tumultuous 1970s America, Jim Jones is a charismatic church leader, preaching social justice to his growing, diverse congregation. Aiming to create a utopia, he sets up Jonestown, a commune in the jungle of Guyana. What began as a peaceful movement seeking social justice, spirals into a mass casualty event that leaves 918 dead. Told by survivors and eyewitnesses, the series sheds light on the final harrowing hours in Jonestown.

Watch the three-part series Cult Massacre: One Day in Jonestown on Saturday 7th December at 9pm, on National Geographic UK. 📺
